<Base title="About INNO Fiber Optic Temperature Measurement" description="Learn how INNO supports fluorescent fiber optic temperature measurement for transformers and high-voltage industrial equipment."><section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">About INNO</p><h1>Focused on Optical Temperature Measurement</h1><p>{site.companyName} develops fluorescent fiber optic temperature sensing components and monitoring architectures for power equipment and industrial environments.</p></div></section><section class="section"><div class="container prose"><h2>Application-led engineering</h2><p>The useful starting point is not a generic channel count. It is the thermal point, the equipment insulation environment, the installation stage and the decision the temperature value must support. INNO helps translate those inputs into a probe, instrument and integration scope.</p><h2>A focused product boundary</h2><p>This website covers point-based fluorescent fiber optic temperature probes, instruments and related monitoring solutions. It intentionally excludes unrelated transformer accessories and distributed temperature sensing as a primary product category.</p><h2>Specification discipline</h2><p>Model-specific values belong on confirmed datasheets. Where a value has not been confirmed for a selected model, our website says so rather than generalizing across configurations.</p></div></section><CTA/></Base>
